        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add LongCat usage provider",
        "body": "## What\n\nAdds **LongCat** (Meituan) as a usage provider, surfacing token quota (总额度) and fuel-pack balance (加油包) in the menu bar / Overview.\n\n## Why this is a cookie provider\n\nLongCat's public OpenAI/Anthropic-compatible API (`api.longcat.chat`) exposes **no** usage/balance/quota endpoint — every billing/usage path returns 404 and responses carry no rate-limit headers. Usage is only available from the web console (`longcat.chat`) session, so this mirrors the existing **Kimi / MiniMax cookie** providers:\n\n- Automatic import of `longcat.chat` browser cookies, or a manual `Cookie:` header.\n- All cookies for the domain are forwarded (the Meituan-passport auth cookie name is undocumented), rather than keying on a single name.\n\n## Endpoints & mapping (verified against live responses)\n\n| Endpoint | Fields used |\n|---|---|\n| `GET /api/v1/user-current` | `data.name` (account) |\n| `GET /api/lc-platform/v1/tokenUsage` | `data.usage.{totalToken, usedToken, availableToken}` |\n| `GET /api/lc-platform/v1/pending-fuel-packages` | `data.totalQuota` + `data.list[]` |\n\n- Primary window = token quota used %; secondary = fuel-pack balance (with nearest expiry).\n- The `user-current` body is **never logged** (it carries a session token + phone).\n- Decoding tolerates the undocumented `{code,message,data}` envelope and logs the raw shape of the non-sensitive endpoints for future debugging.\n\n## Wiring\n\n`.longcat` added to `UsageProvider` / `IconStyle`, descriptor registry, settings snapshot + builder, implementation registry, logging categories, widget (name/color), cost-usage scanner, and the debug-log switch. Plus brand icon, `docs/configuration.md` provider-id list, CHANGELOG, and unit tests covering the live response shapes.\n\n## Testing\n\n- `swift build` ✅ · `swiftformat` / `swiftlint` ✅ clean\n- `swift test` ✅ (new `LongCatProviderTests` + provider-icon/docs/registry suites pass)\n",
